---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="terms of service" description="n0brains terms of service — the rules of engagement.">
  <section class="about-section legal-page">
    <h1>terms of service</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: May 2025</p>

    <h2>1. acceptance</h2>
    <p>
      By using n0brains Signals ("the Service"), you agree to these terms. If you don't agree,
      don't use the Service. Simple.
    </p>

    <h2>2. description of service</h2>
    <p>
      n0brains Signals provides cryptocurrency market intelligence via REST API, WebSocket, and
      Webhook. The Service aggregates, classifies, and delivers signals from publicly available
      data sources. We do not provide financial advice, trading recommendations, or investment
      counsel. Signals are informational only.
    </p>

    <h2>3. accounts</h2>
    <p>
      You must provide a valid email address to register. You are responsible for keeping your
      API key confidential. If your key is compromised, contact us immediately — we'll rotate it.
      You may not create multiple free-tier accounts to circumvent rate limits.
    </p>

    <h2>4. tiers &amp; billing</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Free tier:</strong> 60 requests/minute, 15-minute signal delay, REST API only. No
      credit card required.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Pro tier:</strong> $19.99/month. 600 requests/minute, real-time signals, full API
      access. Billed monthly via Stripe. You may cancel at any time — access continues through
      the end of your billing period.
    </p>
    <p>
      We reserve the right to change pricing with 30 days' notice. Existing subscribers keep
      their current rate until the next billing cycle after the change.
    </p>

    <h2>5. refunds</h2>
    <p>
      Pro subscriptions are non-refundable. If you cancel, you retain access through the end of
      your paid period. No prorated refunds for partial months.
    </p>

    <h2>6. acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree not to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Resell or redistribute signals without written permission</li>
      <li>Reverse-engineer, scrape, or extract our classification models or source data pipelines</li>
      <li>Use the Service for any illegal purpose</li>
      <li>Attempt to overwhelm, DDoS, or otherwise degrade the Service</li>
      <li>Create multiple free accounts to bypass rate limits</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. disclaimers</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>The Service is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind.</strong> We do not
      guarantee signal accuracy, timeliness, or profitability. Cryptocurrency markets are volatile.
      You can lose money. Past signal performance does not predict future results.
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not financial advisors. Nothing in the Service constitutes investment advice.
      You are solely responsible for your trading decisions.
    </p>

    <h2>8. limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, n0brains shall not be liable for any direct,
      indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Service,
      including but not limited to trading losses, missed opportunities, or data inaccuracies.
      Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid us in the 12 months preceding
      the claim.
    </p>

    <h2>9. intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      The n0brains name, logo, and Service design are our property. Signal data derived from
      public sources is not proprietary, but our classification methodology, scoring algorithms,
      and API structure are. Don't copy them.
    </p>

    <h2>10. termination</h2>
    <p>
      We may suspend or terminate your account for violations of these terms, with or without
      notice. You may delete your account at any time by emailing
      <a href="mailto:support@n0brains.com">support@n0brains.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>11. changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms periodically. Material changes will be communicated via email
      to registered users. Continued use after changes constitutes acceptance.
    </p>

    <h2>12. governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of the jurisdiction in which n0brains operates.
      Any disputes shall be resolved in the courts of that jurisdiction.
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top: 48px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
      // questions? <a href="mailto:support@n0brains.com">support@n0brains.com</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legal-updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 2rem !important;
  }

  .legal-page ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .legal-page li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .legal-page li::before {
    content: "—";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }
</style>